231
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Oh, I think he really supported treating the ones that was injured and all of the blood is saddering.

232
00:22:54,000 --> 00:23:01,000
He was dealing with all, he didn't, he didn't want to be reluctant at all about treating them bad.

233
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:07,000
Like some of the doctors, called C like I said, they took them to the commis, but they were not treating them.

234
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:13,000
And he was glad to be able to.

235
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:16,000
And did he know that you were somewhat involved in the movement?

236
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Yes, he knew, he knew.

237
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:35,000
And during my time in working with Dr. Shirley, they offered a course down in Baker County, the commissioners offered a free course to take on emergency care.

238
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:40,000
They ride on the ambulance, you know, they have to see about our people.

239
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:46,000
And they have no blacks worked on the ambulance at that time.

240
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:56,000
And I would work at Dr. Shirley's office, get off at five o'clock and at night I took this course in emergency medicine.

241
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:04,000
And I was, you know, one of the first, I was the first black really to complete the course in the kind of, and work at night.

242
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:13,000
I was called on duty, maybe 11 o'clock and had to be the doctor's office around nine in the morning.

243
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:20,000
But I just felt like we needed to try to help our people.

244
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:27,000
And since the opportunity was offered to try and help other than other people having to help your people all the time,

245
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:37,000
whether or not, don't know whether we were going to get justice, you know, I felt that we had someone of our color to help with our color.

246
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:45,000
And all other colors who had emergency, it would be a whole lot better in the county.

247
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:49,000
And so he was the one who recommended you for the course?

248
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,000
No, no, no, after.

249
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:57,000
You didn't recommend me for the course after I heard they were all fainting the course free.

250
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
And this was an opportunity.

251
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,000
Now we worked, we worked on the ambulance free.

252
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,000
You took the, they offered the course.

253
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:08,000
They paid for the course, but you had to work free.

254
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:14,000
And I worked on the ambulance, you know, getting up all the time of the night, day and night.

255
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:22,000
But until that free service went out, I worked until that free service went out on the ambulance and Baker County.

256
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,000
