He finally got a little bit calmer than he was at the beginning.

327
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:32,000
And that was, you know, people used to be afraid to even come to Baker County.

328
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:36,000
Because he was going to stop him and you surely was going to get a ticket.

329
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:44,000
You know, they would go around miles like Ron Camilla if they want to go to the Bainbridge to keep them coming to Baker County.

330
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:49,000
He was just, he was just a mean, he just was a mean man.

331
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:59,000
I can say, he had a service station and he put up signs and, you know, doing all of them demonstration and everything that he only wanted white business.

332
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
He didn't want black business.

333
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:09,000
But he finally, to Eel had, I don't know, he had a stroke or something.

334
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
And he stayed down for years before his death.

335
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
Oh, well, I say a separate one.

336
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:19,000
And that's how, you know, things kind of got a little better in Baker County.

337
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,000
Okay.

338
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:25,000
